{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1058,"text":"What's one thing that every person\nin this room is going to become?"},{"time":5174,"text":"Older."},{"time":6375,"text":"And most of us are scared stiff\nat the prospect."},{"time":8965,"text":"How does that word make you feel?"},{"time":11813,"text":"I used to feel the same way."},{"time":13828,"text":"What was I most worried about?"},{"time":15634,"text":"Ending up drooling\nin some grim institutional hallway."},{"time":19311,"text":"And then I learned that only\nfour percent of older Americans"},{"time":22518,"text":"are living in nursing homes,"},{"time":23931,"text":"and the percentage is dropping."},{"time":26151,"text":"What else was I worried about?"},{"time":28270,"text":"Dementia."},{"time":29704,"text":"Turns out that most of us\ncan think just fine to the end."},{"time":32873,"text":"Dementia rates are dropping, too."},{"time":34806,"text":"The real epidemic is anxiety\nover memory loss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37735,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39619,"text":"I also figured that old people\nwere depressed"},{"time":42159,"text":"because they were old\nand they were going to die soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45632,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47405,"text":"It turns out that the longer people live,"},{"time":49383,"text":"the less they fear dying,"},{"time":50906,"text":"and that people are happiest at\nthe beginnings and the end of their lives."},{"time":54659,"text":"It's called the U-curve of happiness,"},{"time":56680,"text":"and it's been borne out\nby dozens of studies around the world."},{"time":60009,"text":"You don't have to be a Buddhist\nor a billionaire."},{"time":62609,"text":"The curve is a function of the way\naging itself affects the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67128,"text":"So I started feeling a lot better\nabout getting older,"},{"time":70434,"text":"and I started obsessing about why\nso few people know these things."},{"time":75359,"text":"The reason is ageism:"},{"time":77029,"text":"discrimination and stereotyping\non the basis of age."},{"time":81175,"text":"We experience it anytime someone assumes\nwe're too old for something,"},{"time":85086,"text":"instead of finding out who we are\nand what we're capable of,"},{"time":88410,"text":"or too young."},{"time":89907,"text":"Ageism cuts both ways."},{"time":92279,"text":"All -isms are socially constructed\nideas -- racism, sexism, homophobia --"},{"time":97594,"text":"and that means we make them up,"},{"time":99798,"text":"and they can change over time."},{"time":102128,"text":"All these prejudices\npit us against each other"},{"time":105151,"text":"to maintain the status quo,"},{"time":107317,"text":"like auto workers in the US competing\nagainst auto workers in Mexico"},{"time":111463,"text":"instead of organizing for better wages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114070,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":115983,"text":"We know it's not OK to allocate\nresources by race or by sex."},{"time":120398,"text":"Why should it be OK to weigh\nthe needs of the young against the old?"},{"time":124587,"text":"All prejudice relies on \"othering\" --\nseeing a group of people"},{"time":128247,"text":"as other than ourselves:"},{"time":129695,"text":"other race, other religion,\nother nationality."},{"time":133196,"text":"The strange thing about ageism:"},{"time":135518,"text":"that other is us."},{"time":138226,"text":"Ageism feeds on denial --\nour reluctance to acknowledge"},{"time":141216,"text":"that we are going to become\nthat older person."},{"time":144650,"text":"It's denial when we try\nto pass for younger"},{"time":147824,"text":"or when we believe in anti-aging products,"},{"time":150762,"text":"or when we feel like our bodies\nare betraying us,"},{"time":153598,"text":"simply because they are changing."},{"time":156227,"text":"Why on earth do we stop celebrating\nthe ability to adapt and grow"},{"time":160193,"text":"as we move through life?"},{"time":162200,"text":"Why should aging well mean\nstruggling to look and move"},{"time":165368,"text":"like younger versions of ourselves?"},{"time":167877,"text":"It's embarrassing\nto be called out as older"},{"time":170024,"text":"until we quit being embarrassed about it,"},{"time":172119,"text":"and it's not healthy to go through life\ndreading our futures."},{"time":175277,"text":"The sooner we get off\nthis hamster wheel of age denial,"},{"time":178737,"text":"the better off we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181641,"text":"Stereotypes are always\na mistake, of course,"},{"time":183743,"text":"but especially when it comes to age,"},{"time":185493,"text":"because the longer we live,"},{"time":186854,"text":"the more different\nfrom one another we become."},{"time":189022,"text":"Right? Think about it."},{"time":190423,"text":"And yet, we tend to think of everyone\nin a retirement home"},{"time":193173,"text":"as the same age: old --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":195067,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":196608,"text":"when they can span four decades."},{"time":199062,"text":"Can you imagine thinking that way\nabout a group of people"},{"time":201753,"text":"between the ages of 20 and 60?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204638,"text":"When you get to a party, do you head\nfor people your own age?"},{"time":207885,"text":"Have you ever grumbled\nabout entitled millennials?"},{"time":211639,"text":"Have you ever rejected a haircut\nor a relationship or an outing"},{"time":215165,"text":"because it's not age-appropriate?"},{"time":217539,"text":"For adults, there's no such thing."},{"time":219783,"text":"All these behaviors are ageist."},{"time":221842,"text":"We all do them,"},{"time":223537,"text":"and we can't challenge bias\nunless we're aware of it."},{"time":226698,"text":"Nobody's born ageist,"},{"time":228058,"text":"but it starts at early childhood,"},{"time":229748,"text":"around the same time attitudes\ntowards race and gender start to form,"},{"time":233222,"text":"because negative messages\nabout late life bombard us"},{"time":236678,"text":"from the media and popular\nculture at every turn."},{"time":240054,"text":"Right? Wrinkles are ugly."},{"time":241651,"text":"Old people are pathetic."},{"time":243192,"text":"It's sad to be old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245043,"text":"Look at Hollywood."},{"time":246458,"text":"A survey of recent\nBest Picture nominations"},{"time":248586,"text":"found that only 12 percent\nof speaking or named characters"},{"time":252383,"text":"were age 60 and up,"},{"time":253913,"text":"and many of them\nwere portrayed as impaired."},{"time":257025,"text":"Older people can be\nthe most ageist of all,"},{"time":259091,"text":"because we've had a lifetime\nto internalize these messages"},{"time":262359,"text":"and we've never thought to challenge them."},{"time":264863,"text":"I had to acknowledge it"},{"time":266373,"text":"and stop colluding."},{"time":268101,"text":"\"Senior moment\" quips, for example:"},{"time":270348,"text":"I stopped making them when it dawned on me"},{"time":272396,"text":"that when I lost\nthe car keys in high school,"},{"time":274538,"text":"I didn't call it a \"junior moment.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":276298,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":278759,"text":"I stopped blaming\nmy sore knee on being 64."},{"time":281910,"text":"My other knee doesn't hurt,"},{"time":283478,"text":"and it's just as old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284978,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287014,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":288331,"text":"We are all worried about\nsome aspect of getting older,"},{"time":291293,"text":"whether running out of money,"},{"time":292905,"text":"getting sick, ending up alone,"},{"time":295306,"text":"and those fears are legitimate and real."},{"time":298264,"text":"But what never dawns on most of us"},{"time":300000,"text":"is that the experience of reaching old age"},{"time":302134,"text":"can be better or worse\ndepending on the culture"},{"time":304769,"text":"in which it takes place."},{"time":306755,"text":"It is not having a vagina\nthat makes life harder for women."},{"time":310055,"text":"It's sexism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311293,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313212,"text":"It's not loving a man that makes\nlife harder for gay guys."},{"time":315985,"text":"It's homophobia."},{"time":317308,"text":"And it is not the passage of time\nthat makes getting older"},{"time":320920,"text":"so much harder than it has to be."},{"time":322533,"text":"It is ageism."},{"time":323886,"text":"When labels are hard to read"},{"time":325492,"text":"or there's no handrail"},{"time":326857,"text":"or we can't open the damn jar,"},{"time":328541,"text":"we blame ourselves,"},{"time":329939,"text":"our failure to age successfully,"},{"time":332327,"text":"instead of the ageism that makes\nthose natural transitions shameful"},{"time":336345,"text":"and the discrimination that makes\nthose barriers acceptable."},{"time":340515,"text":"You can't make money off satisfaction,"},{"time":342529,"text":"but shame and fear create markets,"},{"time":345231,"text":"and capitalism always needs new markets."},{"time":348369,"text":"Who says wrinkles are ugly?"},{"time":350104,"text":"The multi-billion-dollar\nskin care industry."},{"time":353302,"text":"Who says perimenopause and low T\nand mild cognitive impairment"},{"time":357195,"text":"are medical conditions?"},{"time":358512,"text":"The trillion-dollar\npharmaceutical industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360926,"text":"(Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361981,"text":"The more clearly we see\nthese forces at work,"},{"time":364135,"text":"the easier it is to come up\nwith alternative, more positive"},{"time":367439,"text":"and more accurate narratives."},{"time":370335,"text":"Aging is not a problem to be fixed\nor a disease to be cured."},{"time":374904,"text":"It is a natural, powerful,\nlifelong process that unites us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380732,"text":"Changing the culture is a tall order,\nI know that, but culture is fluid."},{"time":384870,"text":"Look at how much the position\nof women has changed in my lifetime"},{"time":388209,"text":"or the incredible strides\nthat the gay rights movement"},{"time":390758,"text":"has made in just a few decades, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":392844,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393892,"text":"Look at gender."},{"time":395383,"text":"We used to think of it\nas a binary, male or female,"},{"time":398064,"text":"and now we understand it's a spectrum."},{"time":400254,"text":"It is high time to ditch\nthe old-young binary, too."},{"time":403872,"text":"There is no line in the sand\nbetween old and young,"},{"time":406546,"text":"after which it's all downhill."},{"time":408522,"text":"And the longer we wait\nto challenge that idea,"},{"time":410807,"text":"the more damage it does\nto ourselves and our place in the world,"},{"time":414869,"text":"like in the workforce,\nwhere age discrimination is rampant."},{"time":418646,"text":"In Silicon Valley, engineers\nare getting Botoxed and hair-plugged"},{"time":422115,"text":"before key interviews --"},{"time":423467,"text":"and these are skilled\nwhite men in their 30s,"},{"time":425972,"text":"so imagine the effects\nfurther down the food chain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428468,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430654,"text":"The personal and economic\nconsequences are devastating."},{"time":434049,"text":"Not one stereotype about older workers\nholds up under scrutiny."},{"time":438219,"text":"Companies aren't adaptable and creative\nbecause their employees are young;"},{"time":442321,"text":"they're adaptable and creative despite it."},{"time":445294,"text":"Companies --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":446473,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":447561,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":450177,"text":"We know that diverse companies\naren't just better places to work;"},{"time":453279,"text":"they work better."},{"time":454488,"text":"And just like race and sex,\nage is a criterion for diversity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459053,"text":"A growing body of fascinating research"},{"time":461113,"text":"shows that attitudes towards aging"},{"time":462830,"text":"affect how our minds and bodies\nfunction at the cellular level."},{"time":466380,"text":"When we talk to older people\nlike this (Speaks more loudly)"},{"time":469250,"text":"or call them \"sweetie\" or \"young lady\" --"},{"time":471249,"text":"it's called elderspeak --"},{"time":472600,"text":"they appear to instantly age,"},{"time":474627,"text":"walking and talking less competently."},{"time":477575,"text":"People with more positive\nfeelings towards aging"},{"time":479891,"text":"walk faster,"},{"time":481087,"text":"they do better on memory tests,"},{"time":482698,"text":"they heal quicker, and they live longer."},{"time":486014,"text":"Even with brains\nfull of plaques and tangles,"},{"time":488655,"text":"some people stayed sharp to the end."},{"time":491175,"text":"What did they have in common?"},{"time":492853,"text":"A sense of purpose."},{"time":494183,"text":"And what's the biggest obstacle\nto having a sense of purpose in late life?"},{"time":497685,"text":"A culture that tells us that getting older\nmeans shuffling offstage."},{"time":501827,"text":"That's why the World Health\nOrganization is developing"},{"time":504622,"text":"a global anti-ageism initiative"},{"time":506234,"text":"to extend not just\nlife span but health span."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510074,"text":"Women experience the double whammy"},{"time":512107,"text":"of ageism and sexism,"},{"time":513771,"text":"so we experience aging differently."},{"time":516300,"text":"There's a double standard\nat work here -- shocker --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":519171,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":520463,"text":"the notion that aging enhances men\nand devalues women."},{"time":524637,"text":"Women reinforce this double standard\nwhen we compete to stay young,"},{"time":528986,"text":"another punishing and losing proposition."},{"time":531661,"text":"Does any woman in this room really believe"},{"time":534405,"text":"that she is a lesser version --"},{"time":536415,"text":"less interesting, less fun in bed,\nless valuable --"},{"time":539835,"text":"than the woman she once was?"},{"time":542434,"text":"This discrimination affects our health,"},{"time":544342,"text":"our well-being and our income,"},{"time":546095,"text":"and the effects add up over time."},{"time":548600,"text":"They are further compounded\nby race and by class,"},{"time":551255,"text":"which is why, everywhere in the world,"},{"time":553491,"text":"the poorest of the poor\nare old women of color."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557488,"text":"What's the takeaway from that map?"},{"time":559509,"text":"By 2050, one out of five of us,"},{"time":561941,"text":"almost two billion people,"},{"time":563711,"text":"will be age 60 and up."},{"time":565757,"text":"Longevity is a fundamental hallmark\nof human progress."},{"time":569252,"text":"All these older people represent a vast\nunprecedented and untapped market."},{"time":575269,"text":"And yet, capitalism and urbanization\nhave propelled age bias"},{"time":579205,"text":"into every corner of the globe,"},{"time":581268,"text":"from Switzerland,\nwhere elders fare the best,"},{"time":583710,"text":"to Afghanistan, which sits at the bottom\nof the Global AgeWatch Index."},{"time":588720,"text":"Half of the world's countries\naren't mentioned on that list"},{"time":591605,"text":"because we don't bother to collect data\non millions of people"},{"time":595221,"text":"because they're no longer young."},{"time":597596,"text":"Almost two-thirds of people\nover 60 around the world"},{"time":600454,"text":"say they have trouble\naccessing healthcare."},{"time":603053,"text":"Almost three-quarters say their income\ndoesn't cover basic services"},{"time":606884,"text":"like food, water, electricity,\nand decent housing."},{"time":611214,"text":"Is this the world we want our children,\nwho may well live to be a hundred,"},{"time":615269,"text":"to inherit?"},{"time":616554,"text":"Everyone -- all ages,\nall genders, all nationalities --"},{"time":620593,"text":"is old or future-old,"},{"time":622829,"text":"and unless we put an end to it,\nageism will oppress us all."},{"time":626718,"text":"And that makes it a perfect target\nfor collective advocacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631295,"text":"Why add another -ism to the list\nwhen so many, racism in particular,"},{"time":635328,"text":"call out for action?"},{"time":637140,"text":"Here's the thing:"},{"time":638397,"text":"we don't have to choose."},{"time":640191,"text":"When we make the world\na better place to grow old in,"},{"time":642910,"text":"we make it a better place\nin which to be from somewhere else,"},{"time":646075,"text":"to have a disability,"},{"time":647633,"text":"to be queer, to be non-rich,\nto be non-white."},{"time":651289,"text":"And when we show up at all ages\nfor whatever cause matters most to us --"},{"time":655710,"text":"save the whales, save the democracy --"},{"time":658459,"text":"we not only make\nthat effort more effective,"},{"time":661013,"text":"we dismantle ageism in the process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664036,"text":"Longevity is here to stay."},{"time":666377,"text":"A movement to end ageism is underway."},{"time":668912,"text":"I'm in it, and I hope you will join me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672239,"text":"(Applause and cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676595,"text":"Thank you. Let's do it! Let's do it!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":681207,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}